<hr><a name="_details"></a><h2>Detailed Description</h2>
Interface with a microphone allowing to record sound samples. 
<p>
The typical way to use this class to record a sound follws: <div class="fragment"><pre class="fragment">  <a class="code" href="classarv_1_1Microphone.html#a0">Microphone</a> micro;
  <span class="keywordflow">if</span> (!micro.init()) error();
  micro.alloc(5.0f);  <span class="comment">// ready to record 5 seconds of sound</span>
  micro.start();      <span class="comment">// start recording ...</span>
  sleep(5);           <span class="comment">// wait 5 seconds for the sound to record</span>
  micro.stop();       <span class="comment">// ... stop recording</span>
  <span class="keywordflow">if</span> (micro.save(<span class="stringliteral">"record.wav"</span>))
      std::cout &lt;&lt; <span class="stringliteral">"&gt; sound sample saved successfuly."</span> &lt;&lt; std::endl;
  <span class="keywordflow">else</span>
      std::cout &lt;&lt; <span class="stringliteral">"&gt; error while saving sound sample."</span> &lt;&lt; std::endl;
  micro.close();
</pre></div>
